Amplitude is a comprehensive digital analytics and product intelligence platform that provides organizations with tools to understand user behavior, optimize product experiences, and drive growth through data-driven insights. The platform consists of four core products that work together to deliver end-to-end product analytics capabilities.

## Core Product Suite

**Amplitude Analytics** serves as the foundational product for behavioral analytics, enabling teams to track, measure, and analyze user interactions across digital products. It provides deep insights into user journeys, conversion funnels, and product performance metrics.

**Amplitude Data** functions as the data management and governance layer, ensuring data quality, consistency, and accessibility across the organization. It handles data ingestion, transformation, and distribution to various downstream systems including data warehouses.

**Amplitude Experiment** delivers feature flagging and experimentation capabilities, allowing teams to safely deploy features, run A/B tests, and make data-driven product decisions through controlled rollouts and statistical analysis.

**Amplitude Session Replay** captures and reconstructs user sessions, providing visual insights into user behavior patterns, identifying friction points, and enabling teams to understand the qualitative aspects of user interactions.

## Integration Architecture

The platform operates through a multi-layered integration approach utilizing both SDKs and APIs. **Amplitude SDKs** provide client-side integration capabilities across various platforms and programming languages, enabling seamless data collection from web, mobile, and server-side applications. The **Amplitude APIs** offer programmatic access to platform functionality, supporting data ingestion, querying, and management operations.

The **Session Replay Browser package** (@amplitude/session-replay-browser) represents a specialized component that integrates with the broader Amplitude ecosystem. It utilizes the amplitudeEngagement.boot method for initialization, supporting both basic configuration with user_id parameters and advanced setup through AmplitudeBootOptions. This configuration system allows for comprehensive user property mapping, device identification, and session tracking customization.

## Key Technical Components

The platform's technical architecture centers around event-based data collection and analysis. Core concepts include **event properties** for capturing interaction metadata, **user properties** for maintaining user state and characteristics, and **device identification** for cross-session user tracking. The **Browser SDK 2** represents the latest iteration of web-based data collection capabilities.

Feature flagging functionality enables controlled feature releases and experimentation workflows, while data warehouse integration capabilities ensure that Amplitude data can be synchronized with existing data infrastructure and analytics tools.

